		<td><b>Can someone run an MMC2/MMC4 test ROM for us?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />FHorse is trying to use my test ROM to get MMC2 and MMC4 support working in puNES. But I want to make sure that the test ROM itself is correct. I don't want it to be relying on differences between the emulators and PowerPak on which I tested it and the actual hardware. So I'll need someone to rip up one of these NES or Famicom games, solder in EPROM sockets.<br /><ul><li>Mike Tyson's Punch-Out!! </li><li>Punch-Out!! </li><li>Famicom Wars </li><li>Fire Emblem </li><li>Fire Emblem Gaiden </li></ul><br />Then try <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=120164#p120164" class="postlink">Holy Diver Batman</a> on it and tell us what four-digit code it produces.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


