		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The MMC2/MMC4 test kernel in Holy Diver Batman runs in RAM, meaning it could be turned into a hot-swap test ROM. But I'm not quite ready to spend money on doing so myself. To test a hot-swap ROM, I'd have to mod my own front-loading NES to disable the CIC and then buy a copy of MTPO.

		

